SIMPLE: urchin
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Urchin
<hw>Ur"chin</hw> <pr>(⟦ucir⟧"ch⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>urchon</ets>, <ets>irchon</ets>, a hedgehog, OF.
<ets>ire⟦cced⟧on</ets>, <ets>eri⟦cced⟧on</ets>, <ets>heri⟦cced⟧on</ets>,
<ets>herichon</ets>, F. <ets>h⟦eacute⟧risson</ets>, a derivative fr. L.
<ets>ericius</ets>, from <ets>er</ets> a hedgehog, for <ets>her</ets>;
akin to Gr. <grk>chh`r</grk>. Cf. <er>Herisson</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A hedgehog.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A sea urchin. See <er>Sea
urchin</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A mischievous elf supposed sometimes to take the
form a hedgehog.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧We 'll dress [them] like
<xex>urchins</xex>, ouphes, and fairies.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A pert or roguish child; -- now commonly used only
of a boy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And the <qex>urchins</qex> that stand with their thievish eyes⟦br⟧
Forever on watch ran off each with a prize.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Howitt.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You did indeed dissemble, you <qex>urchin</qex> you; but where's
the girl that won't dissemble for an husband?</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>One of a pair in a series of small card cylinders,
arranged around a carding drum; -- so called from its fancied
resemblance to the hedgehog.</def> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Urchin fish</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a
diodon.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Urchin</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Urchin
<hw>Ur"chin</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Rough; pricking; piercing.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Helping all <xex>urchin</xex> blasts.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Urchon</ent>⟦br⟧
